title.narrative: Revenue Administration and Revenue Policy - Argentina. Revenue Policy and Administration - Argentina

description.narrative: Assistance to La Administración Federal de Ingresos Públicos (AFIP) will develop the functions of its Employee Integrity Unit and improve its capacity for internal audit and investigations, with the aim of rooting out corruption in revenue administration. The engagement emphasizes anticorruption measures involving expertise in inspector general functions. Specific corruption deterrent measures include training investigators and auditors in handling internal controls, auditing IT systems security of confidential taxpayer information (and providing recommendations for system upgrades), and creating whistleblower support pathways.. Assistance to La Administración Federal de Ingresos Públicos (AFIP) will develop the functions of its Employee Integrity Unit and improve its capacity for internal audit and investigations, with the aim of rooting out corruption in revenue administration. The engagement emphasizes anticorruption measures involving expertise in inspector general functions. Specific corruption deterrent measures include training investigators and auditors in handling internal controls, auditing IT systems security of confidential taxpayer information (and providing recommendations for system upgrades), and creating whistleblower support pathways. The project could extend past 2019 if it is to be expanded beyond the current scope.. Assistance to La Administración Federal de Ingresos Públicos (AFIP) will develop the functions of its Employee Integrity Unit and improve its capacity for internal audit and investigations, with the aim of rooting out corruption in revenue administration. The engagement emphasizes anticorruption measures involving expertise in inspector general functions. Specific corruption deterrent measures include training investigators and auditors in handling internal controls, auditing IT systems security of confidential taxpayer information (and providing recommendations for system upgrades), and creating whistleblower support pathways. In 2020, the project will expand to support AFIP audit capacity, through implementation of a Quality Review Staff (Q.R.S.) in the general audit unit, and through advancement of the international auditor corps' handling of transfer pricing cases.. Project has ended.

description.narrative: U.S. assistance in Argentina promotes regional stability and nonproliferation, and enhances opportunities for mutually beneficial economic initiatives. The Argentine government's approaches towards international peacekeeping operations (PKO), the nonproliferation of weapons of mass destruction, and counterterrorism are welcome developments. Although the previous Kirchner government placed substantial constraints on security, counternarcotics, and law enforcement cooperation in recent years, the new government, which took office on December 10, has signaled very clearly that it seeks much more robust cooperation with the United States on all of these issues.
